1 including but not limited to the following organizations and entities:
2 (1) the Montana Safe Schools Center;
3 (2) the Office of Public Instruction;
4 (3) the Montana Department of Justice;
5 (4) the Montana Sheriffs and Peace Officers Association;
6 (5) the Board of Public Education;
7 (6) the School Administrators of Montana
8 (7) the Montana School Boards Association;
9 (8) the Department of Public Health and Human Services;
10 (9) the Montana Professional Learning Collaborative;
11 (10) the Montana Board of Crime Control; and
12 (11) the Jeremy Bullock Memorial Trust.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the committee organize the study based on an examination of
14 Montana's implementation of the Ten Essential Actions to Improve School Safety recommended to the Attorney
15 General of the United States by the School Safety Working Group of the Office of Community Oriented Policing
16 Services in 2020, including:
17 (1) a review of best practices in implementing each action, including examples from other states;
18 (2) an analysis of whether, how, and to what degree Montana has implemented best practices for
19 each action; and
20 (3) an examination of how Montana can improve the implementation of each action.
21 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the committee:
22 (1) review existing Montana statutes and funding mechanisms related to school safety, with a
23 specific focus on examining how existing statutes and funding mechanisms can be clarified, coordinated,
24 consolidated, and better aligned with the Ten Essential Actions to Improve School Safety; and
25 (2) examine how cross-agency coordination and collaboration for school safety can be promoted in
26 Montana, including through a designated entity to act as a clearinghouse for model policies, training, and
27 technical assistance.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that all aspects of the study, including presentation and review
